# Proxy Auto-Config (PAC) Files: Technical Overview

## What is a PAC File?

A PAC file is a JavaScript file that defines logic for how a browser or OS should route network requests - determining whether to use a proxy server or connect directly for any given URL.

## Basic Structure

```javascript
function FindProxyForURL(url, host) {
    // Logic here
    return "PROXY proxy.company.com:8080";
    // or
    return "DIRECT";
}
```

This single function is the required entry point - browsers call it for every network request.

## Return Value Options

```javascript
// Use a specific proxy
return "PROXY proxy.company.com:8080";

// Use SOCKS proxy
return "SOCKS5 proxy.company.com:1080";

// Connect directly (bypass proxy)
return "DIRECT";

// Failover chain - try first, fall back
return "PROXY primary:8080; PROXY backup:8080; DIRECT";
```

## Common Enterprise Logic Patterns

### Basic Internal/External Split
```javascript
function FindProxyForURL(url, host) {
    // Internal traffic goes direct
    if (isInNet(host, "10.0.0.0", "255.0.0.0")) {
        return "DIRECT";
    }
    if (isInNet(host, "192.168.0.0", "255.255.0.0")) {
        return "DIRECT";
    }

    // Internal domains go direct
    if (dnsDomainIs(host, ".company.com")) {
        return "DIRECT";
    }

    // Everything else through proxy
    return "PROXY proxy.company.com:8080";
}
```

### Multi-Region Proxy Selection
```javascript
function FindProxyForURL(url, host) {
    var clientIP = myIpAddress();

    // Route based on client subnet to nearest proxy
    if (isInNet(clientIP, "10.1.0.0", "255.255.0.0")) {
        return "PROXY proxy-us-east.company.com:8080";
    }
    if (isInNet(clientIP, "10.2.0.0", "255.255.0.0")) {
        return "PROXY proxy-eu-west.company.com:8080";
    }

    // Default proxy with failover
    return "PROXY proxy.company.com:8080; DIRECT";
}
```

### Application-Specific Routing
```javascript
function FindProxyForURL(url, host) {
    // Cloud services bypass proxy (performance)
    if (dnsDomainIs(host, ".office365.com") ||
        dnsDomainIs(host, ".microsoft.com") ||
        dnsDomainIs(host, ".microsoftonline.com")) {
        return "DIRECT";
    }

    // Specific protocols bypass proxy
    if (url.substring(0, 4) == "ftp:") {
        return "DIRECT";
    }

    // Localhost always direct
    if (host == "localhost" || host == "127.0.0.1") {
        return "DIRECT";
    }

    return "PROXY proxy.company.com:8080";
}
```

## Built-in PAC Helper Functions

| Function | Purpose | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `isInNet(host, net, mask)` | IP range matching | Internal subnet detection |
| `dnsDomainIs(host, domain)` | Domain suffix match | `.company.com` check |
| `shExpMatch(host, pattern)` | Shell wildcard matching | `*.internal.*` |
| `isPlainHostName(host)` | No dots in hostname | Intranet shortnames |
| `myIpAddress()` | Client's IP | Location-based routing |
| `dnsResolve(host)` | Resolve hostname to IP | Dynamic routing decisions |
| `isResolvable(host)` | DNS lookup test | Reachability check |
| `dnsDomainLevels(host)` | Count domain levels | TLD detection |
| `weekdayRange()` | Time-based logic |
